    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/parishes-and-charter-trustees-in-england-2012-to-2013"/>
    <title>Parishes and charter trustees in England 2012 to 2013</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;This release provides accurate information on parishes and charter trustees in England for the financial year 2012-13.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In England in 2012-13 there are 9,967 parishes, 17 charter trustees and 2 Temples of London. This gives a total of 9,986 local precepting authorities.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Of the 9,984 parishes and charter trustees in England, 9,065 are charging a non-zero precept in 2012-13, 50 fewer than the previous year, or a decrease of 0.5 per cent.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The average Band D parish precept in England in 2012-13 is £47.74. This is an increase of £1.76, or 3.8 per cent over 2011-12.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Revisions to 2010-11 and 2011-12 data arising from a number of authorities correcting previously reported data are also included in the release and in the tables below.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
